OL,7,MSinclair Spectrum Double RestorationM  
OL,9,BI owned a Spectrum +2 many years agoBB 
OL,10,Bbut never the original Spectrum. I'd   
OL,11,Bseen a load of pictures on Twitter     
OL,12,Bby ZXWife and thought I'd get a couple 
OL,13,Bof machines to investigate - the       
OL,14,Boriginal rubber keyed Spectrum, and the
OL,15,Blater Spectrum Plus.B                  
OL,16,FI like repairing machines as well as   
OL,17,Fplaying with them, so took a gamble on 
OL,18,Ftwo sold as "untested" on eBay. The    
OL,19,Foriginal Spectrum cost #30 and I paid  
OL,20,F#33 for the Spectrum Plus.    MM       
OL,22,Q]MGvisit me onlineCretroworkshop.uk    
OL,24,ARadioMic BSinclair C5 CNews FMain Index
PN,40202
SC,0002
PS,C000
FL,403,401,404,101,8ff,400
OL,1,BThe original Spectrum was missing its  
OL,2,Bcase screws and smelled of loft.       
OL,3,BNeither machine came with a powersupply
OL,4,Bso I bought one from tfw8bit.com.      
OL,5,FBefore powering up an old Spectrum it  
OL,6,Fis advisable to perform some checks    
OL,7,Fusing a multi-meter. Detecting failed  
OL,8,Fcomponents can prevent further failures
OL,9,Fas the RAM is susceptable to damage. My
OL,10,Fmachines passed all pre-flight checks. 
OL,11,EI replaced all the capacitors as the   
OL,12,ESpectrum doesn't have good ventilation 
OL,13,Eand these are prone to failure. I also 
OL,14,Eadded a simple modification to bypass  
OL,15,Ethe RF modulator, and pass the         
OL,16,Ehigher quality composite video to the  
OL,17,Erear video connector. This involved    
OL,18,Eadding a single capacitor.             
OL,19,AI used a diagnostic cartridge from     
OL,20,ARetroleum that performed checks on the 
OL,21,ARAM, ROM, keyboard and other parts.This
OL,22,Ahighlighted a faulty speaker on the    
OL,23,ASpectrum Plus which was then replaced. 
OL,24,ARadioMic BSinclair C5 CNews FMain Index
PN,40203
SC,0003
PS,C000
FL,403,401,404,101,8ff,400
OL,1,BThe keyboard membrane on the original  
OL,2,BSpectrum was brittle and cracked.The   
OL,3,Bmembrane on the Plus had also suffered 
OL,4,Band was blackened and sticky at the    
OL,5,Bconnector. So both were replaced. The  
OL,6,BPlus then had an issue with certain    
OL,7,Bkeys appearing to be stuck, this was   
OL,8,Bresolved by carefully adjusting the    
OL,9,Bmembrane position.                     
OL,10,FFinally both machines were disassembled
OL,11,Fand given a good scrub with detergent. 
OL,12,FOnce re-assembled the original Spectrum
OL,13,Fwas treated to a brand new faceplate   
OL,14,Fand it looks nearly as good as new.    
OL,15,EI gave both machines a good workout    
OL,16,Eincuding loading games from cassette   
OL,17,Eand SD card, using a DiVMMC Future.    
OL,18,AThe Spectrum is often remembered for   
OL,19,Aits terrible keyboard. I typed in      
OL,20,Athe same BASIC program listing on both 
OL,21,Amachines. The Plus definately has an   
OL,22,Aimproved keyboard, although the        
OL,23,Arubber model was quite useable.        
OL,24,ARadioMic BSinclair C5 CNews FMain Index